The Cold Access Tier is designed for data that is rarely accessed but still needs to be available with relatively quick retrieval.

Characteristics:

* Lower storage cost than Cool
* Higher access cost
* Longer retention period

For example, compliance data accessed once or twice a year.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is audit logs stored for regulatory purposes.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is archived business records.

Cold tier offers further cost savings for rarely accessed data.
